result.name: Emporio Antico

reviews.text: Lovely place for a quiet dinner:D Personally I love the main course a lot and the Kale salad. Can’t wait to come back! The duck cook perfectly...🤤

Emporio Antico has been nominated as one of the best 10 fine dining restaurants with wine pairing in Hong Kong. However, my friend and I were not a big drinking person. But we still enjoyed a delicious and healthy dinner at Emporio Antico with a relatively quiet environment. Most of the items on the menu are vegetarian friendly (except the mains) or gluten-free (for dessert). We had the whole restaurant to ourselves for most of the time. I guess it’s one of the perks of having dinner early.

For starters, you can choose from Kale Caesar Salad, Fontina and Raclette Fondue, or Quinoa Salad. All of them are vegetarian friendly. I chose this cheesy starter and was so satisfied with the grilled fontina cheese and raclette cheese. They were so aromatic, yet not overly oily. They were very enjoyable with the sourdough toast. There was far more cheese than toast, so after I finished all my toast, I ate the cheese like mochi as it got quite sticky once it’s cooled. This starter is very filling indeed.

There are 3 options for mains: Seared Chicken Breast, Seared Seabass, Grass Fed Sirloin. I picked the sirloin. It was served with beetroot, mushroom and pepper berry jus. As usual, I went for the sides first. The mushroom was so juicy and flavoured; the beetroot was so sweet and enjoyable. As for the berry jus, it tasted like beetroot to me even though it’s yellow and in the shape of a pear.

The sirloin is very delicious. I was surprised that I wasn’t asked how would I want my sirloin to be cooked. I guess it doesn’t really matter when the steak is grilled right to the point so that you have a crunchy grilled surface with juicy and tender meat underneath. Yum!

The meal ended with a yummy gluten-free dessert. Either a Dark Chocolate Cake or Berry Trifle. I chose the dark chocolate cake. It has a hint of coconut oil flavour (like most of the gluten free desserts). The dense and moist texture make the cake a lit one and very enjoyable. I adore the heavy chocolate flavour as well as the chocolate nibs on the plate. It did make a perfect full stop to the meal.
Great tasting healthy food! The chocolate cake especially is amazing. Will definitely be back.

Penne was okay
Scallops over cooked
Fish was good
Duck breast ok
Some of the Fries were burnt
The tuna tartar was in chunks so not really a tartar and has the tendon in there so tendinous when it shouldn’t be
Carrot sweet potato salad was ok
The apple crumble Was sugar free and tasted like baby food...too bad

Overall a mediocre experience 

Thanks
Cosy n quiet! Love the black truffles pasta
